- Comment section requests
- Related search terms
- Adjacent topics they haven't explored
- Beginner vs advanced content balance
- Format variations (tutorials vs breakdowns vs reviews)

Give me 20 video ideas that fill these gaps.</div>

            <div class="code-block">TEMPLATE 3: FULL VIDEO SCRIPT GENERATOR

Write a YouTube video script for a [VIDEO LENGTH] video about [TOPIC].

**My Channel Info:**
- Niche: Type Beat Producer
- Target audience: Rappers, singers, content creators looking for beats
- Tone: Confident, helpful, authentic
- Unique angle: [What makes you different]

**Video Goal:** [Educate/Entertain/Showcase beat/Sell]

**Script Requirements:**
- STRONG hook in first 10 seconds that creates curiosity
- Clear promise of value delivery
- 3-5 main points with smooth transitions
- Pattern interrupts every 60-90 seconds
- Personal story or example to build connection
- Clear CTA at end (subscribe + free download/purchase link)
- Natural, conversational language (not corporate)

**Structure:**
1. Hook (0:00-0:15) - Open with question, shocking statement, or bold claim
2. Intro (0:15-0:45) - Who I am, what we're covering, why it matters
3. Main Content (with timestamps)
4. Recap (last 30 seconds)
5. CTA

Include [CUES IN BRACKETS] for B-roll, graphics, or editing notes.</div>

            <div class="code-block">TEMPLATE 4: BEAT BREAKDOWN SCRIPT

